This is the central observation of the present analysis. The evaluation-scale degree of freedom---the freedom to evaluate each quark mass at any of several reference scales rather than at its self-scale---appears to account for most of the apparent significance seen in multi-triple Koide-quark searches. Sign choice and triple selection contribute substantially less.

